Package com.amazonaws.kinesisvideo.parser.utilities

Class MkvChildElementCollector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazonaws.kinesisvideo.parser.mkv.MkvElementVisitor
      • com.amazonaws.kinesisvideo.parser.utilities.MkvChildElementCollector
  • public class MkvChildElementCollector
extends MkvElementVisitor
    This collects and stores all the child elements for a particular master element. For MkvDataElements, it copies the values and stores them to make sure they can be accessed after the iterator for the mkvstream parser has moved on.

      • equivalent

        public boolean equivalent​(List<MkvElement> otherChildren)
        Check if the collected children in this collector are the same as those from another collection ? We are not checking for full equality since the element number embedded in the meta-data wll be different. It compares the typeinfo and the saved values.
        Parameters:
        otherChildren - The children of the other collector.
        Returns:
        True if the typeinfo and the saved values of the children of the other collector are the same.
